# Borsuk-Ulam

Borsuk-Ulam is a Python library to compute antipodal points on the sphere from ECMWF data files

## Requirements
pip install ecmwf-open-data xarray numpy xarray scipy json logging cfgrib

# get sample data from ECMWF

```python
from ecmwf.opendata import Client
client = Client()
result  = client.retrieve(step=[0,6],type="cf",param = ["2t","msl","sp"],target="data.grib2",)

## Find ulampoints in the above data file

```python
import findulam
ds = xr.open_dataset('data.grib2',engine='cfgrib')
ulamdata = findulam.ulampoints(ds)

## See what the temperature/pressure ulampoints are
```python
data = ulamdata.sel[variable_1='2t',variable_2='msl'].ulampoints.data
data[0].point
data[1].point

## Find ulampoints at other times **numpy time array needed***
```python
findulam.ulampoints(ds,step = [0,1,2,3,4,5,6])

## Find ulampoints at one minute intervals between 0h and 1h
```python
findulam.ulampoints(ds,step = [0,1], N=60)

## Restrict to only temperature and pressure
```python
python3 findulam.py -h

